Description: Large corroded iron round swivel ring, of circular cross-section, with a short segment which is thicker around a circular socket for a missing pivoting rod or joint.
Curator's comments: The "large swivel ring (xxxvii. 18) (...) probably a part of chariot fittings", mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 78 § 77, p. 110.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 78 § 77, p. 110, pl. xxxvii, 18)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.79, p.185, pl.27)
